.TH COUNTRY-BLOCK 8 "March 2026" "country-block" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
country-block \- manage country-based firewall blocking
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B country-block
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B country-block
maintains ipsets from country IP block lists and applies iptables and
ip6tables rules based on
.IR /etc/country-block/config.conf .
.PP
The command must be run as root when changing firewall state.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B apply
Restore cached ipsets from
.I /var/cache/country-block/ipsets.save
and apply firewall rules from the configuration file.
.TP
.B update
Download current country IP block lists for the configured countries, update
the matching ipsets, save the resulting ipset state, and run
.BR "country-block apply" .
.SH SYSTEMD UNITS
.TP
.B country-block.service
Runs
.B country-block apply
during boot to restore cached ipsets and firewall rules. It is enabled by
default when the package is installed.
.TP
.B country-block.timer
Runs weekly and triggers
.BR country-block-update.service .
It is enabled and started by default when the package is installed.
.TP
.B country-block-update.service
Oneshot helper used by
.BR country-block.timer .
It runs
.B country-block update
and is not enabled directly.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/country-block/config.conf
Country, chain, and IP-version configuration.
.TP
.I /var/cache/country-block/
Downloaded country lists and saved ipset state.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ipset (8),
.BR iptables (8),
.BR ip6tables (8),
.BR curl (1)
